channel.title: No-ip Help
channel.description:
Alright.
See, my server won't run of 43594. And when I try it, the no-ip address doesn't let me in, or anyone else.
BUT it does work when I do 5555, only for me though. When I set the port as 5555, and forward that port it works. It doesn't let anyone else in using that no-ip though. I used " chillz.servegame.org " because I used DYNDNS to get my thing.
I tried www.no-ip.com but that didn't work so I went with that one.
Only problem I have now is trying to get other people in.
(*My firewall is at "trusting". *In my system services, in my firewall, I added chillzscape and with the port off 5555 to 5555 and checked it. * In my routers applications & gaming, I added ports 5555 to 5555, added the end of my ip and checked it. * My routers firewall is also disabled. )
Anyone know what might be stopping other people from getting in?
